<subSubSection box="[151,590,963,990]" pageId="9" pageNumber="104" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,590,963,990]" box="[151,590,963,990]" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,590,963,990]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="9" pageNumber="104" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,590,963,990]" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">
On 
<taxonomicName authority="Aurivillius, 1900" authorityName="Aurivillius" authorityYear="1900" box="[198,590,963,990]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Craspedocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,377,963,990]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">Craspedocerus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Aurivillius, C." box="[383,590,963,989]" pageId="9" pageNumber="104" pagination="409 - 421" refId="ref4204" refString="Aurivillius, C. (1900) Verzeichniss der von Dr. F. Meinert im Jahre 1891 in Venezuela gesammelten Cerambyciden. Ofversigt Svenska Vetenskaps-Akademiens Forhandlingar, 57, 409 - 421." type="journal article" year="1900">Aurivillius, 1900</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="104" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1035,1638]" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Aurivillius, C." box="[309,514,1035,1061]" pageId="9" pageNumber="104" pagination="409 - 421" refId="ref4204" refString="Aurivillius, C. (1900) Verzeichniss der von Dr. F. Meinert im Jahre 1891 in Venezuela gesammelten Cerambyciden. Ofversigt Svenska Vetenskaps-Akademiens Forhandlingar, 57, 409 - 421." type="journal article" year="1900">Aurivillius (1900)</bibRefCitation>
regarding 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Aurivillius" authorityYear="1900" box="[640,810,1035,1061]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Craspedocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[640,810,1035,1061]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">Craspedocerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(translated): “antennomeres III–V tumid, dense setose ventrally;” and “Closely related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lepeletier de Saint Fargeau &amp; Audinet-Serville" authorityYear="1830" box="[546,675,1072,1097]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Ptericoptus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[546,675,1072,1097]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">Ptericoptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1868" box="[730,819,1071,1097]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[730,819,1071,1097]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">Bisaltes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but immediately distinguished from both by the elongated lower eye lobes.” Of these features, only the densely setose ventral surface of antennomeres III–V may, eventually, be used to separate this subgenus, because the other species currently included in it do not have the basal antennomeres distinctly tumid as in the 
<typeStatus box="[598,646,1180,1206]" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">type</typeStatus>
species (
<taxonomicName authority="Aurivillius, 1900" authorityName="Aurivillius" authorityYear="1900" box="[750,1073,1179,1206]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Craspedocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="poecilus">
<emphasis box="[750,876,1179,1206]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">C. poecilus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Aurivillius, C." box="[881,1073,1179,1205]" pageId="9" pageNumber="104" pagination="409 - 421" refId="ref4204" refString="Aurivillius, C. (1900) Verzeichniss der von Dr. F. Meinert im Jahre 1891 in Venezuela gesammelten Cerambyciden. Ofversigt Svenska Vetenskaps-Akademiens Forhandlingar, 57, 409 - 421." type="journal article" year="1900">Aurivillius, 1900</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1088,1171,1179,1205]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–35. 27" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[204,1387,181,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-18@8.[200,1387,181,1836]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 27–35. 27) Bisaltes buquetii Thomson, 1868, holotype female. 28) Bisaltes triangularis Breuning, 1940, holotype. 29) Bisaltes flaviceps Breuning, 1940, holotype. 30–31) Bisaltes fuscodiscalis Breuning, 1943, holotype female: 30) Dorsal habitus; 31) Basal antennomeres. 32) Bisaltes (Craspedocerus) ptericoptoides Breuning, 1942, holotype 33) Bisaltes pictus Breuning, 1940, holotype. 34) Craspedocerus poecilus Aurivillius, 1900, syntype male. 35) Bisaltes columbianus Breuning, 1971, holotype. Figures 27–34 by Jesus Santiago Moure; figure 35 by John Chemsak." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825637" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825637/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
)).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1035,1638]" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">
<bibRefCitation author="Breuning, S." box="[199,385,1215,1241]" pageId="9" pageNumber="104" pagination="113 - 175" refId="ref4484" refString="Breuning, S. (1942) Novae species Cerambycidarum. XI. Folia Zoologica et Hydrobiologica, 11, 113 - 175." type="journal article" year="1942">Breuning (1942)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Aurivillius" authorityYear="1900" box="[521,691,1215,1241]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Craspedocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[521,691,1215,1241]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">Craspedocerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1868" box="[890,979,1215,1241]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[890,979,1215,1241]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">Bisaltes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and reported (translated): “Very close to 
<taxonomicName authority="Auriv." authorityName="Aurivillius" authorityYear="1900" box="[151,326,1251,1277]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Craspedocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="poecilus">
<emphasis box="[151,244,1251,1277]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">poecilus</emphasis>
Auriv.
</taxonomicName>
, but the lower eye lobes noticeably longer than the genae, prosternal process somewhat recurved backward, the metatibiae not so excessively extended; the elytra without a postmedian dark band.” Later, 
<bibRefCitation author="Breuning, S." pageId="9" pageNumber="104" pagination="209 - 335" refId="ref4683" refString="Breuning, S. (1971 a) Revision des especes americaines de la tribue des Apomecynini Lac. (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae). Entomologische Abhandlungen aus dem Staatliches Museum fur Tierkunde, 37 (3), 209 - 335." type="journal article" year="1971">Breuning (1971a)</bibRefCitation>
separated 
<taxonomicName box="[361,565,1323,1349]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Bisaltes">
<emphasis box="[361,450,1323,1349]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">Bisaltes</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[467,556,1323,1349]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">Bisaltes</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName box="[636,921,1323,1349]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Craspedocerus">
<emphasis box="[636,725,1323,1349]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">Bisaltes</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[743,913,1323,1349]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">Craspedocerus</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
in his key as follows (translated): “Antennomeres III-V not tumid,” leading to 
<taxonomicName box="[543,747,1359,1385]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Bisaltes">
<emphasis box="[543,632,1359,1385]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">Bisaltes</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[648,737,1359,1385]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">Bisaltes</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
; “These articles tumid,” leading to 
<taxonomicName box="[1145,1431,1359,1385]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Craspedocerus">
<emphasis box="[1145,1234,1359,1385]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">Bisaltes</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1250,1420,1359,1385]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">Craspedocerus</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Even so, 
<bibRefCitation author="Breuning, S." box="[259,461,1395,1421]" pageId="9" pageNumber="104" pagination="209 - 335" refId="ref4683" refString="Breuning, S. (1971 a) Revision des especes americaines de la tribue des Apomecynini Lac. (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae). Entomologische Abhandlungen aus dem Staatliches Museum fur Tierkunde, 37 (3), 209 - 335." type="journal article" year="1971">Breuning (1971a)</bibRefCitation>
, incomprehensibly, included 
<taxonomicName authority="Breuning, 1940" authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1940" box="[796,1082,1395,1421]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pictus">
<emphasis box="[796,896,1396,1421]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">B. pictus</emphasis>
Breuning, 1940
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1099,1183,1395,1421]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–35. 27" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[204,1387,181,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-18@8.[200,1387,181,1836]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 27–35. 27) Bisaltes buquetii Thomson, 1868, holotype female. 28) Bisaltes triangularis Breuning, 1940, holotype. 29) Bisaltes flaviceps Breuning, 1940, holotype. 30–31) Bisaltes fuscodiscalis Breuning, 1943, holotype female: 30) Dorsal habitus; 31) Basal antennomeres. 32) Bisaltes (Craspedocerus) ptericoptoides Breuning, 1942, holotype 33) Bisaltes pictus Breuning, 1940, holotype. 34) Craspedocerus poecilus Aurivillius, 1900, syntype male. 35) Bisaltes columbianus Breuning, 1971, holotype. Figures 27–34 by Jesus Santiago Moure; figure 35 by John Chemsak." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825637" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825637/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
) in 
<taxonomicName box="[1231,1436,1395,1421]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Bisaltes">
<emphasis box="[1231,1320,1395,1421]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">Bisaltes</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1338,1427,1395,1421]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">Bisaltes</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Breuning, 1942" authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1942" box="[200,576,1431,1457]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ptericoptoides">
<emphasis box="[200,392,1431,1457]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">B. ptericoptoides</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Breuning, S." box="[401,576,1431,1457]" pageId="9" pageNumber="104" pagination="113 - 175" refId="ref4484" refString="Breuning, S. (1942) Novae species Cerambycidarum. XI. Folia Zoologica et Hydrobiologica, 11, 113 - 175." type="journal article" year="1942">Breuning, 1942</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[592,675,1431,1457]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–35. 27" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[204,1387,181,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-18@8.[200,1387,181,1836]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 27–35. 27) Bisaltes buquetii Thomson, 1868, holotype female. 28) Bisaltes triangularis Breuning, 1940, holotype. 29) Bisaltes flaviceps Breuning, 1940, holotype. 30–31) Bisaltes fuscodiscalis Breuning, 1943, holotype female: 30) Dorsal habitus; 31) Basal antennomeres. 32) Bisaltes (Craspedocerus) ptericoptoides Breuning, 1942, holotype 33) Bisaltes pictus Breuning, 1940, holotype. 34) Craspedocerus poecilus Aurivillius, 1900, syntype male. 35) Bisaltes columbianus Breuning, 1971, holotype. Figures 27–34 by Jesus Santiago Moure; figure 35 by John Chemsak." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825637" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825637/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
) in 
<taxonomicName box="[722,1008,1431,1457]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Craspedocerus">
<emphasis box="[722,811,1431,1457]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">Bisaltes</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[828,998,1431,1457]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">Craspedocerus</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
, although both have a similar general appearance and identical antennal shape. 
<bibRefCitation author="Galileo, M. H. M. &amp; Martins, U. R." box="[609,893,1467,1493]" pageId="9" pageNumber="104" pagination="379 - 383" refId="ref4891" refString="Galileo, M. H. M. &amp; Martins, U. R. (2003) Notas e descricoes em Bisaltes Thomson, 1868 e Ptericoptus Lepeletier &amp; Audinet-Serville, 1830 (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae, Apomecynini). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 47 (3), 379 - 383. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0085 - 56262003000300003" type="journal article" year="2003">Galileo &amp; Martins (2003)</bibRefCitation>
transferred 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1940" box="[1027,1124,1468,1493]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pictus">
<emphasis box="[1027,1124,1468,1493]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">B. pictus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<emphasis box="[1157,1182,1468,1493]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">B.</emphasis>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Aurivillius" authorityYear="1900" box="[1197,1367,1467,1493]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Craspedocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1197,1367,1467,1493]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">Craspedocerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Furthermore, still more incomprehensibly, 
<bibRefCitation author="Breuning, S." box="[592,791,1503,1529]" pageId="9" pageNumber="104" pagination="285 - 288" refId="ref4726" refString="Breuning, S. (1971 b) Neue Lamiinae aus den Bestanden des Zoologischen Museums der Humboldt-Universitat in Berlin (Col., Cerambycidae). Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin, 47 (2), 285 - 288. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / mmnz. 19710470206" type="journal article" year="1971">Breuning (1971b)</bibRefCitation>
included 
<taxonomicName authority="Breuning, 1971" authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1971" box="[901,1256,1503,1529]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="columbianus">
<emphasis box="[901,1075,1503,1529]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">B. columbianus</emphasis>
Breuning, 
<quantity box="[1200,1256,1503,1529]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.00634" pageId="9" pageNumber="104" unit="in" value="1971.0">1971</quantity>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1868" box="[1291,1380,1503,1529]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1291,1380,1503,1529]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">Bisaltes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis box="[1396,1420,1504,1529]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">B.</emphasis>
), although the antennae are identical to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Aurivillius" authorityYear="1900" box="[651,774,1539,1565]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Craspedocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="poecilus">
<emphasis box="[651,774,1539,1565]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">B. poecilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is important to note that there are other species currently included in 
<taxonomicName box="[285,489,1575,1601]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Bisaltes">
<emphasis box="[285,374,1575,1601]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">Bisaltes</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[391,480,1575,1601]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">Bisaltes</emphasis>
)
</taxonomicName>
with the ventral surface of the basal antennomeres somewhat densely setose, as for example, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Burmeister, 1865)" baseAuthorityName="Burmeister" baseAuthorityYear="1865" box="[260,648,1611,1638]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Bisaltes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adustus" subGenus="Bisaltes">
<emphasis box="[260,284,1612,1637]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">B.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[300,325,1612,1637]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="104">B.</emphasis>
) 
